{{Infobox figure skater |name= Cynthia Kauffman |image= Bundesarchiv Bild 183-G0313-0018-001, Cynthia Kauffmann, Ronald Kauffman.jpg |caption= |fullname= Cynthia Diane Kauffman |altname= |country= [[United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1948|8|23}} |birth_place= [[Seattle]] |hometown= |residence= |death_date= |death_place= |height= {{height|m=1.60|precision=0}} |partner= [[Ronald Kauffman]] |formerpartner= |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= Seattle SC |retired= |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry| [[United States]]}} {{MedalSport | Pairs' [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[World Figure Skating Championships|World Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze| [[1968 World Figure Skating Championships|1968 Geneva]]|Pairs}} {{MedalBronze| [[1967 World Figure Skating Championships|1967 Vienna]]|Pairs}} {{MedalBronze| [[1966 World Figure Skating Championships|1966 Davos]]|Pairs}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalGold| [[1969 North American Figure Skating Championships|1969 Oakland]]|Pairs}} {{MedalGold| [[1967 North American Figure Skating Championships|1967 Montreal]]|Pairs}} {{MedalSilver| [[1965 North American Figure Skating Championships|1965 Rochester]]|Pairs}} }} '''Cynthia Diane Kauffman''' ([[married name]]: Marshall; born August 23, 1948 in [[Seattle, Washington]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]]. With brother [[Ronald Kauffman]], she a four-time (1966â1969) [[United States Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national champion]] and a three-time (1966â1968) [[World Figure Skating Championships|World bronze medalist]].<ref>{{PDFlink|1=[http://www.sportcentric.com/vsite/vfile/page/fileurl/0,11040,4844-148238-165454-56217-0-file,00.pdf ISU Official Results: World Figure Skating Championships - Pairs]}}</ref> They represented the [[United States at the 1964 Winter Olympics]] and the [[United States at the 1968 Winter Olympics|1968 Winter Olympics]], placing [[figure skating at the 1964 Winter Olympics|8th in 1964]] and [[figure skating at the 1968 Winter Olympics|6th in 1968]].
They were inducted into the [[U.S. Figure Skating Hall of Fame]] in 1995.<ref>[http://www.worldskatingmuseum.org/Museum_HOF_Inductees.htm Hall of Fame Members: UNITED STATES HALL OF FAME ]</ref>
